      <hedline>
        <hl1>Extra Steady For Extra Virgin</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Florence Fabricant</byline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Glugging is not olive oil's style. Slipping out of the bottle in a smooth, thin stream is more like it, and for this a classic stopper-pourer really helps. This one, $2 at Dean &amp; DeLuca, 560 Broadway (Prince Street), has a tiny cap that covers the pouring spout, letting you keep it there for storage. It serves well atop bottles of vinegar or soy sauce, too.</p>
      </block>
